@jimmyfrasche we've "tried" the vendor experiment and we've got an imperfect solution (how do you test all packages and subpackages on Windows?)

I think that what @fortytw2 suggested makes a lot more sense in the context of "try"-ing, but it introduces the problem that it would basically split the language in two, those who use it and those who don't.

As for we'll just merge this in master until code freeze then we'll revert it if it doesn't work, I don't have concrete proof but I tend to believe that aside from _very_ knowledgeable gophers, nobody is using go from master for production, so I don't see how this trying and reverting in case we realize it's not going to work will happen.
